of this event.

00:01:06.890 --> 00:01:09.560
She just has such an
amazing story and path

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:10.880
to get to this point.

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:12.713
And I'll give you a
little bit of background

00:01:12.713 --> 00:01:14.890
about her musical history.

00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:20.157
She started on the
piano at the age of six.

00:01:20.157 --> 00:01:22.240
Got her start singing
professionally in children's

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:24.170
theater at the age of 11.

00:01:24.170 --> 00:01:27.940
She graduated from Harvard
University with honors.

00:01:27.940 --> 00:01:31.140
She also has a Master's
Degree in Voice Performance

00:01:31.140 --> 00:01:33.970
and Pedagogy from Westminster
Choir College in Princeton, New

00:01:33.970 --> 00:01:36.520
Jersey.

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:40.230
She is a classically
trained singer, a soprano.

00:01:40.230 --> 00:01:43.450
She's done opera and has
performed in six languages.

00:01:43.450 --> 00:01:45.980
She's sung internationally
at festivals.

00:01:45.980 --> 00:01:48.480
Has performed here in New
York City at Lincoln Center

00:01:48.480 --> 00:01:50.960
and Carnegie Hall, as well.

00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:52.460
Again, so happy that she's here.

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:54.560
Please give a warm
welcome to Candice Hoyes.

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:57.560
